Readme.md
   968‚Üí### .parse() and .parseAsync()
   970‚ÜíCall with no parameters to parse `process.argv`. Detects Electron and special node options like `node --eval`. Easy mode!
   971‚Üí
   972‚ÜíOr, call with an array of strings to parse, and optionally where the user arguments start by specifying where the arguments are `from`:
   973‚Üí
   974‚Üí- `'node'`: default, `argv[0]` is the application and `argv[1]` is the script being run, with user arguments after that
   975‚Üí- `'electron'`: `argv[0]` is the application and `argv[1]` varies depending on whether the electron application is packaged
   976‚Üí- `'user'`: just user arguments
   977‚Üí
   978‚ÜíFor example:
   979‚Üí
   980‚Üí```js
